Nov 18 2009 	Everything we wanted and more...	We have just arrived back from a 4 night stay at the Oasis. It was quite simply an amazing apartment hotel! The apartment was huge and very well serviced, cleaned daily and bathroom and kitchen stocked with amenities and products. The view we had from the 26th floor was of he neighbouring marina and the palm, both made for breathtaking scenes every morning and when the sun goes down a wonderfully lit city awaits you from the comforts of your balcony. We were given complementary beach towels every day and made the short walk across the street to the beach. The area outside the hotel is brilliant &quot;the walk&quot; - lots of shops and places to eat.We were 2 couples sharing, but could recommend this hotel for all types - families, groups etc. Staff very pleasant every day, good choice for breakfast every morning - including pork station for those who like their bacon sarnies and full english!I would definitely return to this hotel again!	
Nov 3 2009 	Wonderful	I stayed in the Tower in a three + bedroomed apartment with friends and 2 children. I have to say I couldnt fault it on any grounds. 100% clean and service was tip top. We had a sea view and the Palm Beach resort was only a stones throw away. The only mild problem was all the construction work around Dubai although I cant say we were really bothered or inconvenienced by it. The amenities of the nearby hotel are available for guests in the apartments including the pool, bar and restaurants. Great trips are arranged by the hotel daily and dont miss the 'desert safari' or a visist to the old town souks and spice market. And if you want a little pampering, there is a small but busy beauty salon in the hotel also. Evening entertainment was a little thin on the ground in the hotel itself but really you dont want to be confined to the hotel anyway .. go and explore Dubai with its many restaurants,clubs and bars. I would definately recommend the Oasis Beach Apartments to anyone in preference to the hotel anyday.	
Oct 7 2009 	A great family holiday an experienced that has left a lasting impression!	We were pleasantly surprised on arriving at our hotel/apartment. We stayed in a three bedroomed apartment, all with ensuites. The rooms were big, bright, spacious and well furnished. They were kept meticulously clean throughout our stay.The kitchen had all the mod cons. We recieved more than we could drink of bottled water daily as well as a welcome pack with milk, butter and other basic foodstuffs. The beds were so cosy and comfortable, nobody wanted to get out of them in the morning. We travelled as a family of 5 kids(including a teenage son) and 2 adults . The swimming pool was nice and clean, there were three seperate pools, one for childern, a deep pool and one that was about 4&quot; deep. There was always a lifeguard and beach towels were surplus.Because we travelled at the beginning of Ramadam(muslim fasting season) we were a bit worried because of the fasting and not being able to eat out in public until evening, but as it goes, this really did not affect us much.We never really left the apartment until after 2pm on most days because we never got to bed the previous night until about 2am. Trust me you really dont miss much because everything and everywhere in Dubai closes late, I mean really late.The beauty of having an apartment as opposed to a hotel suite for me is the flexibilty of being able to cook for yourself if you want to. I know that when most people travel, the last thing they want to do is end up in the kitchen, however when you are a family of 7, eating out 3 times a day for 8 days can soon add up, coupled with the fact that the younger children can be a bit fussy with food.There is a decently stocked supermarket and shopping mall attached to the apartments.We even joined the dvd club when my 6 six year old had had enough of the late nights and just wanted to cuddle up with mummy on the sofa with a bag of popcorn!The staff were excellent and friendly. They always wore a smile were ready to help and advise. The location is excellent for restaurants and prices are quite reasonable. The area is still being developed but that really did not affect us.The only thing I wasnt really impressed with was the breakfast.We only went for breakfast once even though it was a part of our package. So unless you enjoy continental every day............ My children eat cereal,toast every day at home so being on holiday we expected a more robust menu......I mean thats part of what you do on holiday, eat eat eat.Our holiday ended much too quickly. We all agreed that if we were to come again it wuold be for 2 weeks as we only got to do half the things we planned to do. Our children insist we come back to Oasis Beach Tlowers and book the same apartment. I think that speaks for itself!	
