Mar 8 2009 	Location/Price/Size Can't be beat	Stayed 3 nights in Deluxe 3 bedroom apartment, 2 bedrooms with King and 1 bedroom with 2 twin beds for family of 5 and paid Dhs1600 before taxes. Extremely huge apartment. Bathroom in master bedroom as big as a bedroom. Tvs in each room and internet hook up. Kitchen with everything you can imagine and they give you all the basic food like milk, yogurt, cereal free with the apartment. Used the washer/dryer which was nice. The location on &quot;The Walk&quot; is absolutely amazing. The restaurants and shops seem to go on forever for as beyond what the eye can see. We ate at Wagamama which is in the hotel and one our favorite restaurants when we go to Europe. Was lovely and you can order from their menu for room service as well. We ordered a very decent priced waffle, muffin and croissant for breakfast and the teens at cereal which we bought at a small supermarket in the mall connected to the hotel. Downsides were no private beach - but you can go to the public one across the street. The old hotel across the street is being torn down and makes a lot of noise in the morning - it starts before 10am despite what the hotel's website says, but does not disturb you at night. The parking for cars underneath is really inconvenient and the turns are really tight. They have part of the first floor basement roped off for valet for &quot;the walk:, so to have the machine read your parking card, you have to get out of the car since you can't back up due to the ropes. If the management is reading this, please get some parking attendants to park the cars. Housekeeping didn't clean one time until I called at 4pm. We had planned to use the pool, but there is a building (not associated with hotel) being built right over the pool and the workers were looking at everyone in their bathing suits. I do plan to go back to this hotel for sure as we really enjoyed ourselves and as the title states - you can't beat the location, the size of the apartment nor the price. We may make this hotel our regular one in Dubai.	
