Sep 11 2008	Great apartments but dubious location	I have stayed at the Oasis Beach Towers a number of times over the last year or so when I have been in Dubai on business - bookings are made for my by the client. As others say, the apartments are lovely, although it is impossible to open windows in most bedrooms (and I have stayed in various apartments across the property.) However a caution to anyone going on holiday to Dubai, if you choose this property, you are right in the very middle of extensive construction going on around the area - everywhere you look you will see and hear jackhammers and south asian workers out there in the heat. A sit on your balcony will mean you may well be watching lowly paid labourers sweating it out on 12 hour shifts on one of the buildings to the north south east or west of you as you eat your lobster and sip your champagne. Also, you can't walk outside and find a stack of restaurants about - and you cannot walk to them anyway at the moment because the whole area is a construction zone and only recently some restaurants have opened up in the area. So yes, the building you are in is lovely and the apartments want for nothing, but the actual location is not that of a tropical paradise, but of a work in progress.	
