Jun 8 2008 	Smart 	We have just returned from a 5 night stay here (June 2008) and I definitely recommend it if you are looking for a quality apartment to stay in. The tower is situated in the Marina which is undergoing constant construction but that doesn't detract from very smartly appointed and furnished apartments. We had a 2 bedroom deluxe apartment on the 11th floor, to the side of the tower so there was a partial view of the beach/sea. I would suggest asking for a sea view apartment if possible.The staff were helpful and the service was absolutely fine. There are a number of restaurants, shops etc within the tower complex. If you need a taxi, don't reserve one through the front desk as that results in a private hire 4x4 being booked which is more expensive (e.g., fare to the Burj al Arab is approx. 40dhs which is almost 2x more than the regular fare). There is a taxi rank outside the front to the right hand side so just wait there and jump in a regular cab.There was a 1000dhs &amp; 1500dhs pre-authorisation deposit for the restaurants/bars and room respectively so make sure you have sufficient credit clearance on your card. The card doesn't get charged but they need to know if you have sufficient credit in case. The apartment was impeccably clean, spacious and very tastefully furnished - we're talking dark woods &amp; natural light colours. Our apartment had 2 en suite bedrooms, massive living / dining room, a large fully equipped kitchen, a toilet off the hallway, a laundry room and another toilet off the laundry room. The tower is twinned with the Oasis Beach Hotel directly opposite, which affords complimentary access to the private beach.Overall, a great place to stay and superb value.	
