Mar 27 2007 	Vacation next to construction site	No matter how much you pay, very little or a lot, it is not acceptable to have a 4or5 star hotel facing construction site with 24 hour noise coming from there and tens of construction men looking in your window. It is now 25 floors ready from a building next to the BTA and it means that only premium apartments are a bit above it ( and they cost 120 euros more than superior). Noise is terrible up to the 49th floor, so there is no escape. All 2 bedroom apartments have only partial sea view, lower than 30th floor have tiny piece of the seaview and look directly to the construction. Beach at the hotel is great but overcrowded in the morning and daytime (no free sunbeds) and later in the evening no towels left. Room service food was bad. Rooms were spacious but had furniture very office looking. Flower had a sign &quot;don't touch&quot; (maybe it is in somebodys interest to go to Dubai to mess with room flowers...) On our last day evening a person from hotel came to check the room and do inventory. He counted every single teaspoon, knife and fork not to talk about glasses and cups. This made us feel very uncomfortable like they don't trust you even a bit. Anyway, they took a 1500 UAD deposit on arrival to cover all the possible losses and damage. Thought that would cover few teaspoons. Who needs their teaspoons? If they were some special teaspoons for the hotel, I would understand on some level, but they were totally normal 1 dollar teaspoons. Also totally not suitable for families with small children since there is nowhere you can go outside the hotel (everywhere is construction) and they even do not have special trails for baby trolleys to get to the beach. You need to ring a bell for help each time to get down the stairs! From the hotel, you can not get anywhere without taxi, because there is no pavements for walking. Nearest shop (any shop) is a taxi drive away. Service all around seemed like they tolerate you because you pay, but not more than that. If you don't give huge tips, no smile, no thank you. One exception though! Our cleaning guy was very friendly every day and was giving us nice hints, where to go etc. We were actually very surprised from all the positive reviews people give and those were very important for us when we were choosing our destination and hotel. So all together it was very dissapointing experience! Would never go back again!	
Mar 9 2007	Spot on	I am sat in my luxury apartment on my penultimate night in the OBTA. All in all this has been a superb break. I arrived very early from the airport (8am) and although there was no room available immediately, within 30-45 minutes I had been allocated a 2 bedroom deluxe apartment on the 5th floor. The apartments are fantastic, you could easily live in them full time - hugely spacious, very clean, very modern with flat screen LCD's and brand new fitted kitchens, lovely beds, and great spacious bathrooms, plenty of wardrobes and hanging space, infact 10 out of 10 all around.Unfortunately there is masses of building work going on everywhere in this area, and you do feel in the middle of a building site when driving up. My initial room was directly looking over a new tower block. I am a heavy sleeper, so it didn't worry me too much, however when my mate arrived to stay with me for a few nights, after his second night he couldn't bear the noise any more. Apparently the cement mixer went off every hour through the night - all night!! We complained the next morning and were upgraded to an apartment on the 43rd floor - WOW! The apartment is the same identically as the first one, but you can see out for miles, it is much brighter and there is no noise whatsoever. First class.Not used the pool here, as I prefer the beach for the tan potential!! But the pool over at the Oasis Beach Hotel is excellent, and the gardens and private beach immaculately maintained.Staff are friendly and helpful in both the hotel and the apartments.Had room service a couple of nights - nice, reasonably priced food, but been out most nights. Not eaten in the Oasis Beach as I'm not a buffet person, and the Singaporean was full the night we tried so we went elsewhere. We did snack one night in &quot;The Worst Hotel Bar in the World - Charlie Parrots&quot; - my god that place is awful - no atmosphere, pitch black, the DJ turns the music down so he can talk to his mates on his phone - mind you when he's playing &quot;Grease Lightning, Chain Reaction, and Come on Eileen&quot; he can turn it off and pack it away for all I care!! Anyway, this alone is my one grumble - overpriced drinks in a terrible bar - mind you the drinks are on the high side everywhere you go due to it being hotel only drink laws.All in all, excellent, on the pricey side, but great all the same.	
Feb 24 2007	Service with a smile	Just returned from a half term break at the Oasis.We booked a two room premium apartment, but were upgraded to a 240m2 three room (unnecessarily, but better view). The apartments as described previously are extremely well kitted out, including full laundry facilities and a very nice package of food and soft drinks to welcome you.The facilities and restaurants are excellent and the staff throughout the complex live up to the hotel's aim to be the friendliest hotel in Dubai.The Premium lounge on the 33rd floor was a lovely place to stop for a small snack, lunch, afternoon tea or even just a coffee. Everything done quickly and pleasantly, all on Villeroy and Boch!We had a few minor problems with the apartment, which were sorted out almost as soon as I mentioned them (bulb gone, water not hot enough in one of the bathrooms, stereo playing up), but I can't fault the apartments for their quality and even interior design. The bedding was simple high quality Egyptian Cotton and oh so comfortable.The construction was not an issue and in fact quite fascinating - very little noise pollution during our stay.The location is about 10miles out of town, but there is lots to do before you get to town and the taxis are incredibly good value.We had an excellent stay and if you're looking at this review I'd recommend you book the towers - there's too much choice in Dubai, but space and a smile make it a recommend for me.	
Feb 22 2007 	Luxurious and we were spoiled	This was our second visit to the Oasis Beach in 10 months but this time we stayed at the Oasis Beach Tower. It was a special occasion - our 25th Wedding Anniversary, which we shared with friends and family. We booked a 3-bedroom Premium apartment but on arrival this was changed to 2 x 2-bedroom apartments. The apartment type meant we had the Marhaba meet &amp; greet at Dubai airport - driven around and fast tracked through immigration and baggage (the same going home). This facility was absolutely brilliant and we will be talking about it for years to come.The apartments themselves were stunning, spacious and luxurious with lots of goodies in the welcome food pack. After a week, we still had not used all the contents. The views from the apartment were breath-taking, especially as the balcony barrier only came to waist-height - seriously not recommended if you have children.Also included with the accommodation came complimentary breakfasts, which we took over in the Oasis Beach Hotel restaurant; mid-day snacks; afternoon tea; evening nibbles all taken in the Premier Lounge. The only meals we purchased were in the evening and mainly used the hotel's restaurant. Singapura was lovely.The staff greeted you with a warm smile whatever time of day or night and couldn't do enough for you. We made good use of the hotel's free shuttle to Dubai most days but on one occasion decided to take a taxi and ended stuck in traffic for over 3 hours, but it was at 5pm. It was a nightmare. Take a tip and use the free shuttle buses. They leave at various times including 3pm which misses out all the traffic and catches the shops opening for the evening.We had the most fantastic time and hope to return to Dubai in a few years and will undoubtedly stay again at the Oasis Beach Tower. I can't recommend it strongly enough.	
