Jan 5 2007 	Huge apartments	Had a four bedroom apartment for Grandma, us and two kids. It worked perfectly with so much space. Everyone loved the huge plasma screen. Can use the facilities at Oasis Beach Hotel across the way. The restaurants are OK but not that exciting. The best is probably Singapura which has well-prepared food from all over Asia but doesn't have any beers from that direction. The main restaurant relies on serve-yourself buffets at which the food is luke-warm and tastes as though it was cooked hours ago. Our top tip would be to walk along to the Ritz-Carlton where the restaurant quality is more akin to the quality of the apartments with staff both competent and friendly (fairly rare in Dubai!). There's a lack of shops nearby but the ordering service for groceries is efficient and not overpriced.	
