Dec 8 2006	Superb apartments	We had 2 four bedroomed apartments with 3 couple in one and 4 in the other. We have all been away together on many occasions, but this is the first time in apartments. They are big enough for everyone still to have their own space and privacy. Including the maids room, there are 6 toilets in the apartment, so there's no queuing! The rooms are huge. The lounge has 4 coffee tables in the middle of it and there's still masses of space. The master bedroom was the only room with a television and a safe. Fine for a family, but would have been better if all rooms had them. The apartments are spotlessly clean and toiletries etc are replenished every day as required. The welcome pack in the kitchen isn't replenished, but it's fine to get you started. The tower is well soundproofed which was a good job as we're not the quietest of groups. We were on half board, breakfast and lunch or dinner. There are very few restrictions, maybe 1 dish in each restaurant where the voucher only covers half. The food was superb in all of the places - The Bazaar for breakfast and theme nights, The Singapura for oriental and The Oregano for Mediterranean and the Oasis Beach Bar for snacks etc. The house wine is drinkable, but there's others to choose from. The hotel is a little far out and everyone talks about Dubai being a building site, but believe me, this is in the thick of it. The main hotel and the 2 towers (only one is owned by the hotel) are the only things that seem to be complete in the area. However, having said that, it didn't disturb us too much as we were on the 31st floor and. It's fascinating watching them build, but they do work 24-7.We've stayed at the Jumeriah Beach Hotel previously and this is comparible, but different. It's less formal and the staff seem very happy to work there. The beach is much nicer than the one at the Jumeriah Beach Hotel. This one is natural, however, the Palm does have an effect on the tides occasionally.The main hotel is nice, but a little tired. I would always go for the towerI think as someone else said, once everywhere is complete, the prices will be much higher, so get out there now!	
